plate_plan=pd.read_csv(os.getcwd()+"\\20220125 Combinaisons Alya - Expot Platemap.csv", sep=";", encoding='utf8')

Variables created:

conc_dict - mapping sequential place on plate to concentration reference 4: ('3', '0', '1'), 5: ('4', '0', '1'), etc. 1st column is RV, 2nd is VE, 3rd is replicate number

RV_real_conc - map RV concentration to its number 0': 0.0,'1': 50.0, '2': 25.0 in uM

VE_real_conc - map VE concentration to its number 0': 0.0,'1': 50.0, '2': 25.0 in uM

keep only the first 384 rows¶

normalize¶

add a replicate ID¶

add a cell line¶

replace conc01¶

In [6]:
#Getting wells with only RV (resp. only VE) in a dataframe
RV=plate_plan[plate_plan['Object ID']=='Resveratrol']

VE=plate_plan[plate_plan['Object ID']=='VE821']

#dictionnaire conc_dict des concentrations de RV et VE, avec le nom du réplicat
conc_dict={plate_plan['Dest well seq'][i]:(plate_plan['Conc C01'][i], plate_plan['Conc C02'][i], plate_plan['Replicate ID'][i]) for i in plate_plan.index}

#map RV concentration to its number
RV_real_conc={RV['Conc C01'][i] : RV['Well conc (µM)'][i] for i in RV.index}

#map VE821 concentration to its number
VE_real_conc={VE['Conc C02'][i] : VE['Well conc (µM)'][i] for i in VE.index}

2.4 IC50 with the appropriate function¶

2.4.1 Computing IC50 with a conventional function - does not work!¶

In [16]:
import scipy as sp

def flog(x, IC50, slope, m, M):
    return m+(M-m)/(1+np.power(10,(x-IC50)*slope))

3.2 Creating the csv files¶

3.2.1 For the individual replicates¶

In [29]:
pair_index=pd.Series([1 for i in results_per_rep.index])
drug1=pd.Series(['Resveratrol' for i in results_per_rep.index])
drug2=pd.Series(['VE821' for i in results_per_rep.index])
conc1=results_per_rep['Conc RV'] 
conc2=results_per_rep['Conc VE'] 
concunit=pd.Series(['uM' for i in results_per_rep.index])

for rep in ['1', '2', '3']:
    for name in ['WT', 'p53KO', 'SIRT1KO']:
        new_df=pd.concat([pair_index,
drug1,
drug2,
conc1,
conc2,
results_per_rep[name+rep]*100,concunit],axis=1, keys=['PairIndex', 'Drug1', 'Drug2', 'Conc1', 'Conc2', 'Response', 'ConcUnit'], ignore_index=True)
        new_df.to_csv(path_or_buf=os.getcwd()+'/dataframes for SynergyFinder/'+name+rep+'.csv', sep=',', index=False, 
                     header=['PairIndex', 'Drug1', 'Drug2', 'Conc1', 'Conc2', 'Response', 'ConcUnit'])
